  "text": "(ii) Population diversity with different race and types of seizures and epilepsy syndromes may cause variety in AEDs type administration, dosage, and treatment duration. [CITATION_1] However, the data of Bournissen et al (2008) and the current metaanalysis showed no evidence that the ABCB1 C3435T polymorphism is associated with the risk of resistance to AEDs in the Asians and Caucasians. Furthermore, the data were not sufficient enough to allow us to undertake further subgroup analyses on specific subsets of epilepsy types/syndromes and AEDs type. (iii) Variability in the definitions of treatment outcomes to distinguish drugresistance from drug-responsiveness in epilepsy may cause variations in the results. [CITATION_2] Since, those patients who are classified as drug-resistant in some studies may be drug-responsiveness.",
